@startuml
title KafkaCap Data Flow - Message Capture and Deduplication

participant "Message Source\n(Aeron/Multicast/Websocket)" as Source
participant "CaptureDevice\n(Aeron/Multicast/Websocket)" as Capturer
participant "CaptureQueue\n(Memory/Chronicle)" as Queue
participant "BufferedPublisher" as Publisher
participant "Capture Topic 1\n(Kafka)" as Topic1
participant "Capture Topic 2\n(Kafka)" as Topic2
participant "Capture Topic N\n(Kafka)" as TopicN
participant "Deduplicator\n(Consumer Group)" as Dedup
participant "DedupStrategy\n(Sequenced/MultiProducer)" as Strategy
participant "RecordCache" as Cache
participant "RecordPopulator" as Populator
participant "Outbound Topic\n(Kafka)" as Outbound
participant "RecoveryService" as Recovery

== Initialization Phase ==
Recovery -> Outbound: Read last committed offsets
activate Recovery
Outbound --> Recovery: Return offset state
Recovery -> Dedup: Restore deduplication state
deactivate Recovery

== Message Capture Phase (Redundant Devices) ==
Source -> Capturer: Stream message
activate Capturer
Capturer -> Queue: Buffer message
activate Queue
Queue --> Capturer: Buffered
deactivate Queue
Capturer -> Publisher: Publish message
activate Publisher
Publisher -> Topic1: Write to capture topic
activate Topic1
Topic1 --> Publisher: Acknowledgment
deactivate Topic1
deactivate Publisher
deactivate Capturer

Source -> Capturer: Stream message (redundant)
activate Capturer
Capturer -> Queue: Buffer message
activate Queue
Queue --> Capturer: Buffered
deactivate Queue
Capturer -> Publisher: Publish message
activate Publisher
Publisher -> Topic2: Write to capture topic
activate Topic2
Topic2 --> Publisher: Acknowledgment
deactivate Topic2
deactivate Publisher
deactivate Capturer

Source -> Capturer: Stream message (redundant)
activate Capturer
Capturer -> Queue: Buffer message
activate Queue
Queue --> Capturer: Buffered
deactivate Queue
Capturer -> Publisher: Publish message
activate Publisher
Publisher -> TopicN: Write to capture topic
activate TopicN
TopicN --> Publisher: Acknowledgment
deactivate TopicN
deactivate Publisher
deactivate Capturer

== Deduplication Phase ==
Dedup -> Topic1: Poll messages
activate Dedup
activate Topic1
Topic1 --> Dedup: Return messages
deactivate Topic1

Dedup -> Topic2: Poll messages
activate Topic2
Topic2 --> Dedup: Return messages
deactivate Topic2

Dedup -> TopicN: Poll messages
activate TopicN
TopicN --> Dedup: Return messages
deactivate TopicN

loop For each message
    Dedup -> Strategy: Check if duplicate
    activate Strategy
    Strategy -> Cache: Query message key/sequence
    activate Cache
    Cache --> Strategy: Duplicate status
    deactivate Cache
    Strategy --> Dedup: Is unique?
    deactivate Strategy

    alt Message is unique
        Dedup -> Populator: Create Kafka record
        activate Populator
        Populator --> Dedup: Kafka record
        deactivate Populator

        Dedup -> Outbound: Write unique message
        activate Outbound
        Outbound --> Dedup: Acknowledgment
        deactivate Outbound

        Dedup -> Cache: Update cache with message
        activate Cache
        Cache --> Dedup: Updated
        deactivate Cache
    else Message is duplicate
        Dedup -> Dedup: Discard message
    end
end

Dedup -> Topic1: Commit offset
activate Topic1
Topic1 --> Dedup: Committed
deactivate Topic1

Dedup -> Topic2: Commit offset
activate Topic2
Topic2 --> Dedup: Committed
deactivate Topic2

Dedup -> TopicN: Commit offset
activate TopicN
TopicN --> Dedup: Committed
deactivate TopicN

deactivate Dedup

== Back-pressure Handling ==
note over Publisher, Topic1
BufferedPublisher buffers messages
during Kafka outages to handle
back-pressure
end note

@enduml
